"title": "5110: Paul, teaching of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5110",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Paul's understanding of the Christian life was dominated by the importance of Jesus Christ's death and resurrection, by means of which he saw God as having acted decisively to redeem the world. Paul emphasised that Jews and Gentiles alike are justified by faith, and share together in the glorious new era of the Holy Spirit, which is to be consummated at Christ's return.</p>\n<h2>The redeeming work of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>God's work of redemption in Jesus Christ's death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3-Rom8:4\">ROM 8:3–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21-Col1:22\">COL 1:21–1:22</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as substitute, exchanges places with the sinner</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:13–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ reverses the effects of Adam's sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:21–15:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:12–5:19</a></p>\n<h2>The death and resurrection of Jesus Christ mark the beginning of God's new order</h2>\n<h3>New life comes through the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:16-2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:16–5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:7\">EPH 2:4–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13\">COL 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death and resurrection are the basis for a new moral life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:11-Rom6:13\">ROM 6:11–6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:7\">ROM 6:1–6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20-Col3:11\">COL 2:20–3:11</a></p>\n<h3>Those who participate in God's new order are ``in Christ''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:2\">ROM 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:3-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:3–1:14</a> <em>Paul extends the scope of the phrase “in Christ” to include believers, their activity, and the salvation they have received.</em></p>\n<h2>Both Jews and Gentiles are justified by faith</h2>\n<h3>Paul stresses that salvation is by grace through faith alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:21–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16\">ROM 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Jewish works of the law have no role in salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:15-Gal2:16\">GAL 2:15–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:13-Rom4:15\">ROM 4:13–4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:30-Rom10:4\">ROM 9:30–10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:6–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8-Phil3:9\">PHP 3:8–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Both Jews and Gentiles are united in the one body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:13\">1CO 12:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26-Gal3:28\">GAL 3:26–3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:18\">EPH 2:14–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:6\">EPH 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>His indwelling is an integral part of Christian experience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">ROM 8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:1-Acts19:7\">ACT 19:1–19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:2-Gal3:5\">GAL 3:2–3:5</a> <em>Paul's questions suggest that he identifies receiving the Spirit with becoming a Christian.</em></p>\n<h3>He equips the church with gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:1–12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1-1Cor14:33\">1CO 14:1–14:33</a></p>\n<h3>He enables believers to relate to God as Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:6–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:14–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>He guides believers into a right understanding of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:6\">ROM 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:29\">ROM 2:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3-Rom8:4\">ROM 8:3–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:6\">2CO 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>He overcomes believers' sinful human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:8\">ROM 8:5–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:25\">GAL 5:16–5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:8\">GAL 6:8</a></p>\n<h3>He is the guarantee of eternal life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:11\">ROM 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">ROM 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:4-2Cor5:5\">2CO 5:4–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h2>The return of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Paul lived in the hope of the forthcoming personal return of the risen Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:22-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:22–15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:14-1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:14–4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:6-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:6–1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to be raised with Christ upon his return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:14\">1TH 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:12-1Cor15:23\">1CO 15:12–15:23</a></p>\n<h3>The whole created order will be renewed at the return of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:21\">ROM 8:19–8:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a></p>",
